text: Played a poker tournament today*. Turned a set against a flopped straight. All-in. No help on river. Thought I'd busted. But they called me back. I had 6k chips left. Doubled up. Again. Again. Made a great 3-bet value shove on the turn. Before I knew it I had 285k. Top 5 in chips. Then I ran QQ into AA in a huge pot and lost a flip with 88 < AJs and busted 15 minutes later. 🤔 Moral of the story: Never give up in a poker tournament. If you stay patient and stick to your gameplan, there's always a more elaborate and painful bustout awaiting you later. All it takes is a chip and a chair. * Not the Main Event.
